&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Lymington New Forest Hospital are looking for a consultant in geriatric and general medicine to join our consultant team.  We are a small acute hospital located in the beautiful New Forest.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;T&lt;span&gt;his post is designed to add to the current consultant team and improve care for older people within the forest.  There is already an excellent community geriatric service and frailty support team which this post will be linked with to provide integrated care across the patient pathway in the New Forest.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We work closely with University Hospital Southampton and there is opportunity within this post to practice within the Same Day service at UHS if the post holder would like to..  All consultants at Lymington Hospital take part in a general medical on call and keep their own patients from the day of their admission leading to excellent continuity of patient care.  The hospital is innovative and collegiate in its management style and keen to develop the new models of care needed in modern health care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that GMC registration (with a licence to practice) and right to work in the UK are essential for this role. Successful applicants will already have GMC registration or will be able to demonstrate they are eligible. Applicants requiring Tier 2 sponsorship should ensure they meet the Home Office application criteria prior to submitting an application.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information about the post and to arrange a visit to the service, please contact Dr Rachel Anderson Clinical Director on rachel.anderson@southernhealth.nhs.uk &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
